race.comment: BAD DETECTIVE (2) pulled up with an issue last time when well-beaten as one of the favourites. His best form is good enough to win a race in this grade and, if the stable has him right, he will be hard to beat. He draws well and can make his own luck. UNPRAISED (6) drops back in grade after a couple of OK efforts in stronger city races. She maps to get a lovely run and will be finishing hard with no weight on her back. URBANISE (7) is capable of winning this, albeit she is mixing her form so you must take her on trust. MELLIFLUENT (1) is an improving gelding that must be included as a top three chance, while MAGIC PRINCESS (8) doesn't win out of turn but can sneak into the minor money at a big price so it might pay to include her in exotics.
